Source: flag-gems
Section: python
Priority: optional
Maintainer: FlagOS Contributors <contact@flagos.io>
# Phase 1 (current): the .deb is assembled from a pre-built wheel inside the
# 2-stage Dockerfile.deb. Stage 1 (wheel-builder) is the only place that needs
# the heavy build deps (cmake / ninja-build / python3-pybind11 / libtriton-jit-dev);
# Stage 2 (this dpkg-buildpackage step) only unpacks the wheel via pip and
# wraps it. Listing the Stage-1 deps in Build-Depends here would make
# dpkg-checkbuilddeps fail because Stage 2 deliberately does not install them.
#
# Phase 2 (deferred): when we move to a single-stage build that also produces
# libflaggems + libflaggems-dev, add back: cmake (>= 3.20), ninja-build,
# python3-pybind11, libtriton-jit-dev.
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13),
               python3-all,
               python3-pip,
               python3-setuptools,
               python3-wheel,
               dh-python
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/flagos-ai/FlagGems
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/flagos-ai/FlagGems
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/flagos-ai/FlagGems.git
Rules-Requires-Root: no
X-Build-Environment: This package is built in a container that provides
 libtriton-jit-dev (from the FlagOS apt repo) and a CUDA-aware PyTorch.
 The build is done once via scikit-build-core; the resulting wheel is
 split into the binary packages below.

# ---- Phase 1 binary package ----------------------------------------
# python3-flag-gems carries everything (Python + bundled liboperators.so)
# until the cmake-only split (Phase 2) lands.

Package: python3-flag-gems
Architecture: amd64
Depends: python3:any,
         ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         python3-numpy,
         python3-yaml,
         python3-sqlalchemy,
         python3-packaging
# python3-torch is intentionally NOT declared. The distro 'python3-torch'
# is CPU-only and unsuitable for GPU workloads; users install matching
# CUDA torch via pip — see packaging/INSTALL.md.
Recommends: python3-flagtree-nvidia
Description: FlagGems GPU operator library (Python module)
 FlagGems is a GPU operator library written in Triton, providing a
 drop-in replacement for many torch.* operations with custom-tuned
 kernels.
 .
 This package contains the Python bindings, the Triton kernel sources,
 and (for Phase 1 of packaging) the bundled liboperators.so. A future
 release will split the C++ runtime into libflaggems and the headers
 into libflaggems-dev so that downstream C++ consumers can link
 against the operators library without installing the Python module.

# ---- Phase 2 binary packages (DECLARED, not yet built) -------------
# These stanzas ship the C++ side as standalone packages once the
# split lands. Until then, debian/rules does NOT produce them — the
# control file has the names reserved so future PRs are additive.
#
# Package: libflaggems
# Architecture: amd64
# Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libtriton-jit (>= 0.1.0)
# Description: FlagGems GPU operator library (runtime)
#  Standalone C++ runtime (liboperators.so) for hosts that want to use
#  FlagGems kernels via cmake/C++ rather than Python.
#
# Package: libflaggems-dev
# Architecture: amd64
# Depends: libflaggems (= ${binary:Version}), libtriton-jit-dev
# Description: FlagGems GPU operator library (development files)
#  Headers and cmake config for downstream C++ projects linking
#  against libflaggems.
